{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Qingdao Sports Centre Guoxin Gymnasium | nickname = The Diamond | image = Qingdao Guoxin Sport Center Gymnasium.jpg | fullname = Qingdao Sports Centre Guoxin Gymnasium | location = [[Qingdao]], [[China]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = 2005 | built = | opened = 2009 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = Qingdao Conson Development (Group) Co. Ltd | operator = | surface = | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor= | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = [[Qingdao DoubleStar]], [[Qingdao Clipper]] | seating_capacity = 12,500 | }}
'''Qingdao Guoxin Sports Centre Gymnasium''' (official name) is an [[indoor arena|indoor sporting arena]] located in [[Qingdao]], [[China]], used mostly for [[basketball]] and [[arena football]] games. The capacity of the arena is 12,500 spectators. It hosts indoor sporting events such as like badminton, basketball, concerts, gymnastics, table tennis and volleyball.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.2011sudirmancup.com/content/2011-03/30/content_8719058.htm | title=Qingdao Sports Center | publisher=2011sudirmancup.com | date=March 30, 2011 | accessdate=June 8, 2011 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110902214310/http://www.2011sudirmancup.com/content/2011-03/30/content_8719058.htm | archivedate=September 2, 2011 | df= }}</ref>
==Notable Events== *[[Super Show 3]] - [[Super Junior]] The 3rd ASIA Tour, August 28, 2010, with a sold-out crowd of 12,000 people. *[[2011 Sudirman Cup]]
