[[File:TSM350 2015 - Alex Kennedy - Stierch.jpg|thumb|right|2009 winner [[Alex Kennedy (racing driver)|Alex Kennedy]] ''(pictured in 2015)'']] '''INEX Legends Road Course World Finals''' is an annual [[Auto racing|automobile race]] for [[Legends car racing|Legends cars]]. It usually takes place in November at [http://www.racesonoma.com/ Sonoma Raceway], California. During 2008–09 the race was held at [[Las Vegas Motor Speedway]] road course. The World Finals will return to Sonoma for its 14th edition in 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nasaproracing.com/event/1138 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-10-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101030232344/http://www.nasaproracing.com/event/1138 |archivedate=2010-10-30 |df= }}</ref> In 2014 [[Virginia International Raceway]] hosted the event for the first time.
Drivers are divided into three divisions; Pro, Semi-Pro and Masters. In 2009 INEX introduced a new Young Lions category for young drivers between the ages of 12 and 16.
