'''Stade Municipal de Vieux-Habitants''' is a [[association football|football]] stadium in [[Vieux-Habitants]], [[Guadeloupe]]. It has a capacity of 1,000 <ref>https://int.soccerway.com/venues/guadeloupe/stade-municipal-vieux-habitants/ "Soccerway - Stade Municipal, Vieux Habitants" Retrieved 16 August 2011</ref> and is currently used by the [[Guadeloupe Division d'Honneur]]'s reigning champions, [[JS Vieux-Habitants]].
<ref>http://www.weltfussballarchiv.com/Stadion.php?ID=12097 "World Football Archive - Stade Municipal" Retrieved 16 August 2011</ref> In the wake of recent hurricanes, the stadium was renovated in 2004, costing a total of €6.94 million.<ref>http://www.semag.fr/details/55-stade-de-vieux-habitants.html "Immobilier Guadeloupe - Stade de Vieux Habitants" (in French) Retrieved 16 August 2011</ref>

